I made a single-slide infographic on Digital Literacy using a dark theme and simple layout. I divided the content into five parts to make it easy to understand. First, I explained what digital literacy means in simple words. Then, I showed why it is important for students, especially for learning, safety, jobs, and communication.
I also included some useful tools like Google Docs, GitHub, and Canva that students can use in daily work. Another section explains internet safety, such as using strong passwords and avoiding suspicious links. The last part talks about maintaining a professional online presence, especially on LinkedIn.
While making this, I tried to keep the design clean and not too crowded. The difficult part was choosing only important points and fitting them into one slide. Overall, this task helped me learn how to present information in a simple and clear way.
